This paper introduces a new class of reinforcement learning methods, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed algorithm is designed to optimize the cumulative gain over multiple episodes, which involves making decisions based on feedback signals (cs.DS). The paper also mentions applications that involve humans in the loop, such as personalized medical screening and web-based education, indicating a potential connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
